ProtoDefines:
. "We call a nonzero rational number $n$ a congruent number if
   $\pm n$ is the area of a right triangle with rational side 
   lengths. Equivalently, $n$ is a congruent number if the 
   system of two equations $$ a^2+b^2&=&c^2\\ \frac{1}{2}ab&=&n
   $$ has a solution with $a,b,c\in\mathbf{Q}$."
